4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, state-administered death
6 certificates include the date, manner, and location of
7 disposition.
8 This bill would prohibit the inclusion of the
9 date of disposition on state-administered death
10 certificates.
11
12
13 A BILL
14 TO BE ENTITLED
15 AN ACT
16
17 Relating to vital statistics; to amend Section 22-9A-6,
18 Code of Alabama 1975, to prohibit the inclusion of the date of
19 disposition on state-administered death certificates.
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
21 Section 1. Section 22-9A-6, Code of Alabama 1975, is
22 amended to read as follows:
23 "§22-9A-6
24 (a)(1) The board shall by rule determine, by rule, the
25 items or information to be contained on certificates of birth,
26 death, marriage, and divorce and on reports of fetal death and
27 induced termination of pregnancy. Each certificate, report,
28 and other document required by this chapter shall be in a
Page 1

and other document required by this chapter shall be in a
